{{Quote|It's about exploitation, hope, dignity, and identity; it's about what's left inside when everything is taken from you.|Karen Traviss, on ''Republic Commando: Triple Zero''|<ref name="Amazon Blog">{{Amazon|url=gp/blog/A3HJJL4GN2L432|text=Karen Traviss' Amazon Blog|date=2006-02-28}}</ref>}}
'''''Republic Commando: Triple Zero''''' is the second novel in the [[Republic Commando|''Republic Commando'' series]] written by [[Karen Traviss]] and set [[21 BBY/Legends|one year after]] the [[First Battle of Geonosis/Legends|First Battle of Geonosis]]. It tells the story of [[Omega Squad]], [[Delta Squad/Legends|Delta Squad]], a unit of [[Null-class Advanced Recon Commando|Null ARC troopers]], and their [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[General/Legends|Generals]] [[Etain Tur-Mukan]] and [[Bardan Jusik]] as they pursue a [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Separatist]] terror group along the [[Skylane/Legends|skylanes]] and underworld of [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]], known to [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone troopers]] as Triple Zero for its [[Galactic coordinates/Legends|galactic chart coordinates]].

The book contains a short glossary defining ''[[Star Wars]]'', [[Mando'a/Legends|Mando'a]], and military terms. The [[Del Rey]] printing also contains the [[List of short stories|short story]] ''[[Omega Squad: Targets]]'', originally published in [[Star Wars Insider 81|''Star Wars Insider'' #81]], and a preview of ''[[Legacy of the Force: Betrayal]]''. The UK and Australian release printed under the [[Orbit (imprint)|Orbit imprint]] includes the Mando'a glossary, however does not include ''Omega Squad: Targets'' or the preview of ''Betrayal''.

==Publisher's summary==
'''Following the eruption of the bloody Clone Wars at the battle of Geonosis, both sides remain deadlocked in a stalemate that can be broken only by elite warrior teams like Omega Squad, clone commandos with terrifying combat skills and a lethal arsenal&hellip;.'''

''For Omega Squad, deployed deep behind enemy lines, it's the same old special ops grind: sabotage, espionage, ambush, and assassination. But when Omega Squad is rushed to Coruscant, the war's most dangerous new hotspot, the commandos discover they're not the only ones penetrating the heart of the enemy.''

''A surge in Separatist attacks has been traced to a network of Sep terror cells in the Republic's capital, masterminded by a mole in Command Headquarters. To identify and destroy a Separatist spy and terror network in a city full of civilians will require special talents and skills. Not even the leadership of Jedi generals, along with the assistance of Delta squad and a certain notorious ARC trooper, can even the odds against the Republic Commandos. And while success may not bring victory in the Clone Wars, failure means certain defeat.''

==Plot summary==
The novel starts with a flashback [[30 BBY/Legends|eight years before the Battle of Geonosis]] when [[Mandalorian/Legends|Mandalorian]] [[Soldier/Legends|soldier]] [[Kal Skirata]] goes to the rainy [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of Kamino to observe [[Grand Army of the Republic/Legends|the developing army for the Republic]]. He finds out that they are [[Cloning/Legends|cloning]] his friend, [[Jango Fett/Legends|Jango Fett]], and that the [[Cloning/Legends|clones]] have had their age factor doubled. If the clones have lived a year they will have aged two, and when they have lived two years they will have aged four, and so forth. Skirata is disgusted with the [[Kaminoan/Legends|Kaminoans]]' practice of "reconditioning"&mdash;often a term used for terminating&mdash;clone children who didn't pass quality control standards. Six "prototype" ARC Trooper children, designated ''Null''-class, were labeled defective and scheduled for reconditioning because they would not follow any orders given them. However, before the unruly clones can be executed, Skirata intervenes and takes it upon himself to raise and train them personally, keeping them separate from the other clones.

The plot jumps forward to [[22 BBY/Legends|five days after]] the [[First Battle of Geonosis/Legends|Battle of Geonosis]]. Skirata is on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] and has just heard about the conflict and of Jango Fett's death at the hand of [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Mace Windu/Legends|Mace Windu]].

The storyline then skips ahead a [[21 BBY/Legends|year later]], where the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] learns that [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Separatist]] terrorists have infiltrated Coruscant and are spying on the Republic. Skirata is hired by the Republic to track them down and enlists [[Omega Squad]]&mdash;[[Darman Skirata|Darman]], [[Niner Skirata|Niner]], and [[Fi Skirata|Fi]], all personally trained and formally adopted by Skirata, and [[Atin Skirata|Atin]] who was trained by [[Walon Vau]]&mdash;for the mission. Assisting the team is Republic information broker [[Besany Wennen]], Jedi Master [[Arligan Zey]], and [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]] [[Bardan Jusik]] and [[Etain Tur-Mukan]]&mdash;the Jedi who worked with Omega Squad during the [[mission to Qiilura]]. Skirata's [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]] companion [[Enacca]] also joins the group, as does [[Null-class Advanced Recon Commando|Null ARC trooper]] [[Ordo Skirata|Ordo]] and clone trooper [[Corr Skirata|Corr]]. However, the situation is made more complicated when Vau and [[Delta Squad/Legends|Delta Squad]]&mdash;[[Boss (clone commando)/Legends|Boss]], [[Sev/Legends|Sev]], [[Scorch/Legends|Scorch]], and [[RC-1140/Legends|Fixer]]&mdash;also join the team. Skirata and Vau have a rivalry due to their different philosophies in training clone soldiers. Skirata trained Omega Squad as a role model father-figure, while Vau trained Delta Squad through abusive discipline. Atin has a hard history with Vau since he was beaten so many times under his tutelage. During the course of the story, Etain and Darman's relationship grows stronger, and Etain becomes pregnant with Darman's child but does not tell him.

During the mission to track the terrorists down, [[Jinart]] and [[Valaqil]] join in to remind Omega Squad and Etain that they still owe the [[Gurlanin]]s a debt after they helped the clones and Jedi back on [[Qiilura/Legends|Qiilura]]. Etain and Omega Squad promise that they will eventually repay that obligation, but ask the Gurlanins to assist in the mission, to which they agree.

The spies in the Republic are ultimately found, and the information they captured is destroyed and the terrorists are killed. Unfortunately, the rivalry between Omega and Delta Squads remain; Atin and Vau engage in a brutal fistfight that is quickly broken up by [[Bardan Jusik]]. Later, after the celebration of the squads' victory over their mission, Etain reveals to Skirata that she is pregnant with Darman's child. Skirata is angered by this because he believes Etain used Darman. Nevertheless, the two agree to keep this a secret from everyone else&mdash;aside from Jinart and Valaqil&mdash;and that the child will be a Mandalorian like his father and not a Jedi like his mother. Skirata promises Etain that she will be able to go to [[Qiilura/Legends|Qiilura]] and spend some time with Darman. Ordo figures out Etain is pregnant but decides to keep it a secret.

==Development==
In 2005 and 2006, [[Karen Traviss]] claimed on the StarWars.com Message Boards that she had used the 10-month calendar while writing ''Triple Zero'' and the other novels in the ''[[Republic Commando]]'' series<ref name="BCT1">{{SWBoards|url=thread.jspa?threadID=222689&start=1230#13478643|thread=Books, Comics, & Television VIPs|user=[[Karen Traviss]]|date=2005-12-03|time=12:48 PM}}</ref><ref name="BCT2">{{SWBoards|url=thread.jspa?threadID=222689&start=1230#13480202|thread=Books, Comics, & Television VIPs|user=[[Karen Traviss]]|date=2005-12-03|time=4:01 PM}}</ref>&mdash;despite the fact that, in said novels, the one-[[Standard year/Legends|year]] anniversary of the [[First Battle of Geonosis/Legends|First Battle of Geonosis]] occurs approximately twelve months after the battle.<ref name="AnniversaryDates">Karen Traviss's novel ''[[Republic Commando: Hard Contact]]'' dates the [[Battle of Qiilura]] to three [[Standard month/Legends|months]] after the [[First Battle of Geonosis/Legends|First Battle of Geonosis]]. Furthermore, the events of the main section of ''Republic Commando: Triple Zero'', which take place nine months after the Battle of Qiilura, span twenty-eight days and begin on the [[Standard day/Legends|day]] before the one-[[Standard year/Legends|year]] anniversary of the First Battle of Geonosis. Therefore the one-year anniversary of the First Battle of Geonosis must have taken place twelve months after the battle.</ref>

==Continuity==
